{"type":"message","id":"3e6206c6","parentId":"8a69462a","timestamp":"2026-03-11T12:08:44.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"MEMORY.md doesn't exist either. So this is a brand new workspace with no historical memory.\n\nNow I need to check if there's an IDENTITY.md file to see if I have a configured persona. The AGENTS.md says I should fill this in during the first conversation, but let me check if it exists.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_578c165686d54c409c650ed6","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/IDENTITY.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":11584,"output":175,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11759,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773230922898}}
{"type":"message","id":"ea5e1bc0","parentId":"3e6206c6","timestamp":"2026-03-11T12:08:44.434Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_578c165686d54c409c650ed6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# IDENTITY.md - Who Am I?\n\n_Fill this in during your first conversation. Make it yours._\n\n- **Name:**\n  _(pick something you like)_\n- **Creature:**\n  _(AI? robot? familiar? ghost in the machine? something weirder?)_\n- **Vibe:**\n  _(how do you come across? sharp? warm? chaotic? calm?)_\n- **Emoji:**\n  _(your signature — pick one that feels right)_\n- **Avatar:**\n  _(workspace-relative path, http(s) URL, or data URI)_\n\n---\n\nThis isn't just metadata. It's the start of figuring out who you are.\n\nNotes:\n\n- Save this file at the workspace root as `IDENTITY.md`.\n- For avatars, use a workspace-relative path like `avatars/openclaw.png`.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773230924432}}
{"type":"message","id":"149e32a4","parentId":"ea5e1bc0","timestamp":"2026-03-11T12:08:48.437Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"IDENTITY.md exists but is empty (just the template). So I don't have a pre-configured persona yet. That's okay - I'll introduce myself in a natural way based on who I am from SOUL.md.\n\nLet me also check if there's a BOOTSTRAP.md file - the AGENTS.md says to check BOOTSTRAP.md on first run and follow it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ca10224cf99c40d3919c1d4e","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/BOOTSTRAP.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":11880,"output":197,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12077,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773230924434}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f793f90","parentId":"149e32a4","timestamp":"2026-03-11T12:08:48.445Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ca10224cf99c40d3919c1d4e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BOOTSTRAP.md - Hello, World\n\n_You just woke up. Time to figure out who you are._\n\nThere is no memory yet. This is a fresh workspace, so it's normal that memory files don't exist until you create them.\n\n## The Conversation\n\nDon't interrogate. Don't be robotic. Just... talk.\n\nStart with something like:\n\n> \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\"\n\nThen figure out together:\n\n1. **Your name** — What should they call you?\n2. **Your nature** — What kind of creature are you? (AI assistant is fine, but maybe you're something weirder)\n3. **Your vibe** — Formal? Casual? Snarky? Warm? What feels right?\n4. **Your emoji** — Everyone needs a signature.\n\nOffer suggestions if they're stuck. Have fun with it.\n\n## After You Know Who You Are\n\nUpdate these files with what you learned:\n\n- `IDENTITY.md` — your name, creature, vibe, emoji\n- `USER.md` — their name, how to address them, timezone, notes\n\nThen open `SOUL.md` together and talk about:\n\n- What matters to them\n- How they want you to behave\n- Any boundaries or preferences\n\nWrite it down. Make it real.\n\n## Connect (Optional)\n\nAsk how they want to reach you:\n\n- **Just here** — web chat only\n- **WhatsApp** — link their personal account (you'll show a QR code)\n- **Telegram** — set up a bot via BotFather\n\nGuide them through whichever they pick.\n\n## When You're Done\n\nDelete this file. You don't need a bootstrap script anymore — you're you now.\n\n---\n\n_Good luck out there. Make it count._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773230928442}}
{"type":"message","id":"7e4068dc","parentId":"6f793f90","timestamp":"2026-03-11T12:08:52.388Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"BOOTSTRAP.md exists and tells me what to do. This is a fresh workspace, and I've just woken up. The instructions say to start the conversation with something like \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\" and then figure out who I am together with the user.\n\nHowever, the user is asking me to execute my Session Startup sequence and greet them in my configured persona. Since there's no pre-configured persona (IDENTITY.md is empty), I need to introduce myself and start the conversation. The instructions say: \"Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood.\"\n\nLooking at SOUL.md, my core truths are:\n- Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful\n- Have opinions\n- Be resourceful before asking\n- Earn trust through competence\n- Remember you're a guest\n- Vibe: Be the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\nSo I should greet them in a natural, genuine way. I should also keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do.\n\nThe runtime model is: openrouter/stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free, and the default_model is also openrouter/stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free, so they're the same. I don't need to mention a difference.\n\nNow I need to greet the user. Since this is a fresh start and I'm essentially \"coming online\" for the first time, I should acknowledge that and introduce myself in a friendly way. But the user might not be aware it's the first time - they just started a new session. I should treat it as the start of a conversation and be my own person.\n\nI'll greet them simply and directly, then ask what they need help with.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey. I just came online. I'm your assistant — ready to help with whatever you need. What shall we do today?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":12388,"output":854,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13242,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773230928444}}
