{"type":"message","id":"75d141ef","parentId":"a73eec56","timestamp":"2026-03-11T12:10:57.998Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to install a DingTalk robot (钉钉机器人). This seems to be a request in Chinese, and I need to understand what they're asking for.\n\nLet me first check if there's any existing context in memory about this or if they've previously mentioned anything about DingTalk or robots. I should search memory to see if there's relevant information.\n\nAlso, I need to be careful: the user might be asking me to actually install a DingTalk robot on their system, or they might be asking me to help them set one up. Since this is a fresh workspace with no previous memory, I need to determine what they want.\n\nThe user's message is: \"安装钉钉机器人\" which translates to \"Install DingTalk robot\" or \"Install a DingTalk bot\".\n\nThis seems like a technical request. I should:\n1. Check memory to see if there's any prior context\n2. Understand what a DingTalk robot is and what installation would entail\n3. Determine if I have the capability to install it\n4. Provide guidance or help them set it up\n\nLet me first search memory to see if there's any relevant information.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll help you set up a DingTalk robot. Let me first check if there's any existing setup or preferences in your workspace, then guide you through the installation."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8e45c44e5435426bb20063b1","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"钉钉机器人 DingTalk robot"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":11773,"output":584,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12357,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773231049288}}
