ng `plugins` line and then insert the new properties. I'll carefully construct the edit to preserve the current structure.\n\nThe best approach is to replace the existing `\"plugins\": {` line with a multi-line block that includes the new properties. But that could be risky if the formatting changes.\n\nLet me try a different approach: I'll edit the plugins object by inserting the new fields immediately after the opening brace. I can do this by matching the exact line containing `\"plugins\": {` and then inserting after it.\n\nActually, the `edit` tool requires exact text matching. Let me see what the exact text looks like. The current plugins section starts with:\n\n```\n  \"plugins\": {\n    \"entries\": {\n```\n\nI want to insert two lines between the `{` and `\"entries\":`. So I would search for:\n\n```\n  \"plugins\": {\n    \"entries\": {\n```\n\nAnd replace with:\n\n```\n  \"plugins\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"allow\": [\"dingtalk\"],\n    \"entries\": {\n```\n\nLet me do that.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_100d4ad4c785466cb4189ecf","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json","oldText":"  \"plugins\": {\n    \"entries\": {","newText":"  \"plugins\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"allow\": [\"dingtalk\"],\n    \"entries\": {"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":14118,"output":1562,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15680,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773231380266}}
