 a tool. Possibly the user tried to run a command that uses brew to install something.\n\nGiven that the user said \"修复\" (fix), they want me to resolve this issue. I should ask what they are trying to install or whether they want to install Homebrew or install gh via apt.\n\nLet me respond with a clear plan: Since we're on Linux, I recommend installing the needed package (likely gh) directly via apt rather than using Homebrew. I can offer to install it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"The issue is that Homebrew (a macOS package manager) isn't available on this Linux system. To \"fix\" this, we should install the required package directly using apt (or your system package manager).\n\nWhat package were you trying to install? If it's `gh` (GitHub CLI), I can run:\n\n```bash\nsudo apt update && sudo apt install gh\n```\n\nIf you need something else, let me know the package name and I'll install it via apt instead of brew.\n\nOr, if you actually want Homebrew on Linux, I can install it from https://brew.sh, though it's not typical for Linux systems. What's your preference?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":14483,"output":1223,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15706,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773234640427}}
