red. So I can probably run oracle without any files.\n\nBut wait, oracle requires that the binary is installed. Let me check if oracle is installed:\n\n```\nwhich oracle\n```\n\nIf not, I'd need to install it. The skill says \"requires: bins: ['oracle']\" and install instruction: npx -y @steipete/oracle. So I can install it via npx.\n\nBut maybe there's a simpler approach: I can use a direct web search API like DuckDuckGo's HTML or a news API. However, I'd rather use an existing skill if one exists.\n\nLet me check if any skill provides a simple search function. The weather skill is obvious. There's no \"news\" skill listed in the available_skills. The oracle skill is the closest.\n\nGiven the user's request, it's reasonable to use oracle with browser automation to search news about Liu Yifei.\n\nSteps:\n\n1. Ensure oracle is installed.\n2. Run: oracle --engine browser --model gpt-5.2-pro -p \"搜集网上关于刘亦菲的新闻\" (collect online news about Liu Yifei)\n\nBut careful: The prompt should be in Chinese as user wrote Chinese. I'll keep it Chinese.\n\nI need to also consider that the browser mode may require user interaction (like login to ChatGPT?), but the skill says default is browser with GPT-5.2 Pro, and it's a long-running process. That's acceptable.\n\nBut let's first check if oracle is available on the system.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll use the oracle skill to search for news about Liu Yifei (刘亦菲). First, let me check if oracle is installed:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_de53e6cad8dd482895dcf024","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which oracle"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":19415,"output":1613,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21028,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235015477}}
