{"type":"message","id":"4ad3a31b","parentId":"ea8244ab","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:21:00.654Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Not available. I can install it but that would take time.\n\nGiven the complexity, I can just use text processing tools (grep, sed, awk) to extract the needed info from the HTML. I saw that each result block contains:\n\n- Title: inside <h2 class=\"result__title\"><a class=\"result__a\" href=\"...\">TITLE</a></h2>\n- URL: inside <a class=\"result__url\" href=\"...\">DOMAIN/PATH</a>\n- Snippet: inside <a class=\"result__snippet\" href=\"...\">SNIPPET</a>\n\nWe can extract these with grep.\n\nWe need to extract multiple blocks. We can loop through lines and capture between markers. For simplicity, I'll fetch the entire HTML, then use a series of `grep -oP` with PCRE patterns to get the values. But grep -P may not be available. Let's check if grep supports -P.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Check if grep supports PCRE (-P):"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4d48b3ed7536496784258cf5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep --help | grep -i perl"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":34498,"output":436,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34934,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235250236}}
