{"type":"message","id":"a19e03bf","parentId":"eb570ac0","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:21:13.593Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Great, -P is available. So we can use Perl regex to extract.\n\nWe can extract all titles: `grep -oP '(?<=<h2 class=\"result__title\">.*?<a class=\"result__a\" href=\"[^\"]*\">)[^<]+'` but we need to be careful about lines spread across multiple lines. Our grep will work line by line. In the HTML we saw, the title is on the same line as the <a> tag. So we can use:\n\n`grep -oP '<h2 class=\"result__title\">.*?<a class=\"result__a\" href=\"[^\"]*\">\\K[^<]+'`\n\nBut `\\K` is a PCRE feature. Yes.\n\nSimilarly, for URL: `grep -oP '<a class=\"result__url\" href=\"[^\"]*\">\\K[^<]+'`\n\nAnd snippet: `grep -oP '<a class=\"result__snippet\" href=\"[^\"]*\">\\K[^<]+'`\n\nWe'll get multiple lines, then we can paste them together in order. The order of appearance in the HTML is title, then URL, then snippet for each result. So we can number them.\n\nWe could do:\n\ntitles=( $(grep -oP ...) )\nurls=( $(grep -oP ...) )\nsnippets=( $(grep -oP ...) )\n\nBut in shell it's easier to process in one awk script that reads lines and captures these fields.\n\nGiven time, I'll do this:\n\n```\ncurl -s -A \"Mozilla/5.0\" \"https://html.duckduckgo.com/html/?q=刘亦菲+news\" |\nawk '\n  /<h2 class=\"result__title\"/ { \n    match($0, /<a class=\"result__a\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]*)<\\/a>/, a);\n    if (a[1] != \"\") { title = a[1]; has_title=1 }\n  }\n  /<a class=\"result__url\"/ { \n    match($0, /<a class=\"result__url\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]*)<\\/a>/, b);\n    if (b[1] != \"\") { url = b[1]; has_url=1 }\n  }\n  /<a class=\"result__snippet\"/ { \n    match($0, /<a class=\"result__snippet\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]*)<\\/a>/, c);\n    if (c[1] != \"\") { snippet = c[1]; has_snippet=1 }\n    # Print result when we have snippet (complete)\n    if (has_title && has_url && has_snippet) {\n      printf \"标题: %s\\n\", title;\n      printf \"来源: %s\\n\", url;\n      printf \"摘要: %s\\n\\n\", snippet;\n      # reset\n      title=url=snippet=\"\";\n      has_title=has_url=has_snippet=0;\n    }\n  }\n'\n```\n\nBut careful: there might be other lines containing these strings? Possibly not. The pattern: each result block contains those three tags in that order.\n\nLet's test.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll fetch the search results from DuckDuckGo and parse them:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6fbcbc23191e48a68fd74188","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -A \"Mozilla/5.0\" \"https://html.duckduckgo.com/html/?q=刘亦菲+news\" | awk '\n  /<h2 class=\"result__title\"/ {\n    if (match($0, /<a class=\"result__a\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]*)<\\/a>/, a) && a[1] != \"\") {\n      title = a[1]; has_title = 1\n    }\n  }\n  /<a class=\"result__url\"/ {\n    if (match($0, /<a class=\"result__url\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]*)<\\/a>/, b) && b[1] != \"\") {\n      url = b[1]; has_url = 1\n    }\n  }\n  /<a class=\"result__snippet\"/ {\n    if (match($0, /<a class=\"result__snippet\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]*)<\\/a>/, c) && c[1] != \"\") {\n      snippet = c[1]; has_snippet = 1\n    }\n    if (has_title && has_url && has_snippet) {\n      printf \"标题: %s\\n来源: https://%s\\n摘要: %s\\n\\n---\\n\\n\", title, url, snippet\n      title = url = snippet = \"\"\n      has_title = has_url = has_snippet = 0\n    }\n  }\n' | head -n 200","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":34773,"output":1636,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36409,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235260673}}
