{"type":"message","id":"a3809d12","parentId":"e4e9ef21","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:21:27.999Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No output. The awk script didn't match anything. Possibly because the HTML lines are not matching the exact patterns; maybe the tags have extra attributes or newlines. I saw the HTML snippet had `<h2 class=\"result__title\">` on its own line, then the `<a>` on the next line? Actually in the snippet, it was:\n\n```\n<h2 class=\"result__title\">\n  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"result__a\" href=\"...\">刘亦菲近况大反转!...</a>\n</h2>\n```\n\nSo the opening `<a>` is on a separate line, not on the same line as `<h2`. In my awk, I'm only checking each line individually. So the line containing `<h2>` does not contain the `<a>` link. So my pattern fails. I need to capture across lines. That's more complex in awk. Could use `awk` with a record separator of `</div>` for each result block. Then within each block, extract.\n\nSo approach: set RS to `</div>` perhaps, but need to be careful. Simpler: use `grep -Pzo` to extract chunks. `grep -Pzo` can match across newlines with `(?s)`. But easier: use `perl` or `python` if available.\n\nCheck if python is installed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check if Python is available:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ed10908dc852489badbdb7f9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which python3"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":35871,"output":592,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36463,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235274280}}
