{"type":"message","id":"fd1f6ee0","parentId":"855887b6","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:21:40.206Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Great, Python is installed. I can write a small Python script to fetch the page and parse with BeautifulSoup? Not installed. I could use regex or simple parsing with html.parser module. Python's standard library includes `html.parser`. I can parse HTML line by line with a simple state machine.\n\nI'll write a Python script that reads stdin, looks for result blocks, and extracts title, URL, and snippet.\n\nBut maybe easier: use regex on the whole text. Since the HTML is relatively simple and each result block appears as:\n\n```\n<div class=\"result results_links results_links_deep web-result \">\n  <div class=\"links_main links_deep result__body\">\n    <h2 class=\"result__title\">\n      <a ...>TITLE</a>\n    </h2>\n    <div class=\"result__extras\">\n      <div class=\"result__extras__url\">\n        <a ...><img ...></a>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"result__url\" href=\"...\">URL</a>\n    </div>\n    <a class=\"result__snippet\" href=\"...\">SNIPPET</a>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\nSo we can use a regex with re.DOTALL to capture each block: `<div class=\"result results_links results_links_deep web-result \".*?<a class=\"result__snippet\".*?</div>\\s*</div>` maybe.\n\nBut the HTML may have nested divs; the block ends with two closing divs.\n\nAlternatively, I can extract all titles, urls, snippets by scanning for their respective opening tags and capturing content until closing tag.\n\nLet's do a Python script that reads all input, then iterates using a while loop finding occurrences of `<h2 class=\"result__title\">` etc. But note that these tags might be on separate lines; but the HTML is one line? The curl output is likely a single line or multiple lines, but the tags may be separated by newlines. We can read the entire content as a string and then use regex that works across newlines with `re.S`.\n\nWrite a script:\n\n```python\nimport sys, re, html\n\ntext = sys.stdin.read()\n# Find all result items - approximate by splitting on the marker that starts a result: <div class=\"result results_links results_links_deep web-result \"\n# But we'll just find all titles, urls, snippets sequentially.\ntitles = re.findall(r'<h2 class=\"result__title\">\\s*<a [^>]*>([^<]+)</a>', text, re.S)\nurls = re.findall(r'<a class=\"result__url\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]+)</a>', text, re.S)\nsnippets = re.findall(r'<a class=\"result__snippet\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]+)</a>', text, re.S)\n\n# Ensure we have equal count or take min\nn = min(len(titles), len(urls), len(snippets))\nfor i in range(n):\n    # Unescape HTML entities\n    title = html.unescape(titles[i].strip())\n    url = urls[i].strip()\n    snippet = html.unescape(snippets[i].strip())\n    print(f\"标题: {title}\")\n    print(f\"来源: https://{url}\")\n    print(f\"摘要: {snippet}\")\n    print(\"\\n---\\n\")\n```\n\nWe need to unescape HTML entities like `&quot;` etc. Use `html.unescape`.\n\nI'll run this via Python.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll use Python to parse the HTML properly. Let me fetch and parse in one go:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f7f94beaf83b41cbaf93ac26","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nimport sys, re, html, subprocess, urllib.parse\n\n# Fetch the page\nresult = subprocess.run(\n    [\"curl\", \"-s\", \"-A\", \"Mozilla/5.0\", \"https://html.duckduckgo.com/html/?q=刘亦菲+news\"],\n    capture_output=True, text=True\n)\ntext = result.stdout\n\ntitles = re.findall(r'<h2 class=\"result__title\">\\s*<a [^>]*>([^<]+)</a>', text, re.S)\nurls = re.findall(r'<a class=\"result__url\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]+)</a>', text, re.S)\nsnippets = re.findall(r'<a class=\"result__snippet\" href=\"[^\"]*\">([^<]+)</a>', text, re.S)\n\nn = min(len(titles), len(urls), len(snippets))\noutput = []\nfor i in range(n):\n    title = html.unescape(titles[i].strip())\n    url = urls[i].strip()\n    snippet = html.unescape(snippets[i].strip())\n    output.append(f\"标题: {title}\")\n    output.append(f\"来源: https://{url}\")\n    output.append(f\"摘要: {snippet}\")\n    output.append(\"\")\n    output.append(\"---\")\n    output.append(\"\")\n\nprint(\"\\n\".join(output))\nPYEOF","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":36209,"output":1888,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38097,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235288018}}
