{"type":"message","id":"dfc0589d","parentId":"641066dd","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:25:25.706Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to collect Liu Yifei's latest photos from March 10th. This is more specific than just news - they want photos. I should search for images from that date.\n\nI can try searching with DuckDuckGo for images, but they specifically mention \"最新照片\" (latest photos). March 10th is a specific date. Let me try to find image URLs or at least links to galleries.\n\nLet me construct a search: \"刘亦菲 3月10日 照片\" or \"刘亦菲 2026-03-10 图片\".\n\nI'll use DuckDuckGo HTML search again, but this time with image search? DuckDuckGo's image search might be more complex, but I can also use general web search and look for img tags or image URLs.\n\nAlternatively, I could fetch from Nous Infos or Sogou images? But they might block. Let's try Bing image search with a query.\n\nActually, the earlier search results gave us a news snippet about March 10th: \"3月10日，巴黎时装周又现名场面——刘亦菲一身路易威登红色花瓣短裙亮相2026秋冬大秀，从下车瞬间到入场飞吻，直接引爆全球社交媒体。\"\n\nSo there were images from the Paris Fashion Week LV show on March 10. Many articles likely contain images. I can try to extract image URLs from those news pages. That would be more direct: visit the article pages and find the main image or gallery.\n\nBut the request is simply \"搜集3月10日的刘亦菲最新照片\" - collect the latest photos of Liu Yifei from March 10. So the answer could be a list of URLs to images or to articles containing images. I could also list image URLs I find.\n\nSimplify: I'll search for \"刘亦菲 3月10日\" with a site that returns images. Or use Google image search? Let's try a direct image search via DuckDuckGo's i.duckduckgo.com? Actually, DuckDuckGo image search endpoint is something like: https://duckduckgo.com/?q=刘亦菲+3月10日&iax=images&ia=images\n\nBut we need to parse JSON or HTML. DuckDuckGo provides a JSON endpoint? Not sure.\n\nAlternative: Use bing.com/images/search?q=刘亦菲+3月10日\n\nBut I need to fetch and parse.\n\nLet me try Bing images with curl and see if we get JSON? Historically, Bing images have a JSON response at /images/search? ... Actually, the HTML page includes image data in JSON within a script tag with id \"mmEntity\". That's hacky.\n\nSimpler: Since we have Python, we can fetch the HTML of the image search results page and extract <a class=\"iusc\"> tags which contain JSON with image URL. This is typical for Bing.\n\nLet's try with Bing: https://www.bing.com/images/search?q=刘亦菲+3月10日\n\nI'll write a Python script to parse the image search results.\n\nBut careful: the system may have network restrictions? The earlier curl to example.com worked. So let's try.\n\nI'll fetch Bing images search page and parse. I'll write a Python one-liner.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3fecd1a650e94eb38b01f958","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nimport re, json, subprocess, html\n\nquery = \"刘亦菲 3月10日\"\nurl = f\"https://www.bing.com/images/search?q={urllib.parse.quote(query)}\"\n# fetch\nresult = subprocess.run([\"curl\", \"-s\", \"-A\", \"Mozilla/5.0\", url], capture_output=True, text=True)\ntext = result.stdout\n\n# find image data in iusc attributes\npattern = re.compile(r'<a class=\"iusc\".*?m=\\'({.*?})\\'', re.S)\nmatches = pattern.findall(text)\nimages = []\nfor m in matches[:10]:  # top 10\n    try:\n        data = json.loads(html.unescape(m))\n        # image URL is in 'murl'\n        img_url = data.get('murl', '')\n        thumb = data.get('turl', '')\n        title = data.get('t', '') or data.get('pt', '')\n        if img_url:\n            images.append({'title': title, 'url': img_url, 'thumb': thumb})\n    except Exception:\n        continue\n\n# output\nfor img in images:\n    print(f\"标题: {img['title']}\")\n    print(f\"图片链接: {img['url']}\")\n    print(f\"缩略图: {img['thumb']}\")\n    print(\"---\\n\")\nPYEOF","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","m