{"type":"message","id":"58026e11","parentId":"004c0857","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:25:51.127Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HEAD request returned 200 but with content-length: 0, so maybe Bing returns empty for HEAD. The GET might return HTML. My earlier curl to images/search returned no output (empty). Could be that curl is failing due to network restrictions or needing to handle cookies. The HEAD succeeded so connectivity is fine. Let's try to fetch with more options: follow redirects (-L) and maybe add a referer. Also we can use the `-c` and `-b` for cookies. But maybe the issue is that Bing returns compressed content and we need -H \"Accept-Encoding: identity\"? Not needed; curl auto-decompresses if built with zlib.\n\nAlternatively, we can scrape from the news articles we already have, which likely include images. For example, the MSN article: https://www.msn.com/zh-cn/news/other/刘亦菲亮相巴黎时装周造型浪漫-一下车便引全场欢呼-入场时飞吻迷人/ar-AA1XWR08\n\nLet's try to fetch the MSN article and extract the main image. That might be easier than Bing image search.\n\nI'll write Python to fetch the article and look for <meta property=\"og:image\"> or <img> tags.\n\nBut we need only photos from March 10. The news we have includes that date. So we can go to those article URLs and extract images.\n\nLet's pick the MSN article, 163.com article, Tencent news article, Sina, The Paper, Sohu, etc.\n\nI'll write a script to fetch each and extract images.\n\nBut careful: The user said \"搜集3月10日的刘亦菲最新照片\" - collect latest photos from March 10. That likely means photos taken on March 10. The news we retrieved includes March 10 references, and those articles likely contain images. So we can provide direct image URLs.\n\nLet's try to fetch the MSN article page.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7a47d9d340684bef9600542b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nimport urllib.request, re, html, ssl, json, subprocess\nssl._create_default_https_context = ssl._create_unverified_context\n\nurl = \"https://www.msn.com/zh-cn/news/other/%E5%88%98%E4%BA%A6%E8%8F%B2%E4%BA%AE%E7%9B%B8%E5%B7%B4%E9%BB%8E%E6%97%B6%E8%A3%85%E5%91%A8%E9%80%A0%E5%9E%8B%E6%B5%AA%E6%BC%AB-%E4%B8%80%E4%B8%8B%E8%BD%A6%E4%BE%BF%E5%BC%95%E5%85%A8%E5%9C%BA%E6%AC%A2%E5%91%BC-%E5%85%A5%E5%9C%BA%E6%97%B6%E9%A3%9E%E5%90%BB%E8%BF%B7%E4%BA%BA/ar-AA1XWR08\"\n# fetch\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=15) as resp:\n        charset = resp.headers.get_content_charset() or 'utf-8'\n        html_content = resp.read().decode(charset, errors='ignore')\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Error fetching {url}: {e}\")\n    html_content = \"\"\n\n# extract og:image or other images\nimgs = []\n# og:image\nm = re.search(r'<meta\\s+property=\"og:image\"\\s+content=\"([^\"]+)\"', html_content)\nif m:\n    imgs.append(html.unescape(m.group(1)))\n# also look for typical news article featured image: possibly <img.*?data-src=\"...\">\nimgs += re.findall(r'<img[^>]+src=[\"\\']([^\"\\']+)[\"\\']', html_content)\nimgs = [u for u in imgs if u and not u.startswith('data:')]\n# dedup\nseen = set()\nunique_imgs = []\nfor u in imgs:\n    if u not in seen:\n        seen.add(u)\n        unique_imgs.append(u)\n\nprint(f\"从 {url} 找到 {len(unique_imgs)} 张图片:\")\nfor img in unique_imgs[:5]:\n    print(img)\nPYEOF","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":31269,"output":1426,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32695,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235538621}}
{"type":"message","id":"120dc23d","parentId":"58026e11","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:25:51.372Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7a47d9d340684bef9600542b","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"从 https://www.msn.com/zh-cn/news/other/%E5%88%98%E4%BA%A6%E8%8F%B2%E4%BA%AE%E7%9B%B8%E5%B7%B4%E9%BB%8E%E6%97%B6%E8%A3%85%E5%91%A8%E9%80%A0%E5%9E%8B%E6%B5%AA%E6%BC%AB-%E4%B8%80%E4%B8%8B%E8%BD%A6%E4%BE%BF%E5%BC%95%E5%85%A8%E5%9C%BA%E6%AC%A2%E5%91%BC-%E5%85%A5%E5%9C%BA%E6%97%B6%E9%A3%9E%E5%90%BB%E8%BF%B7%E4%BA%BA/ar-AA1XWR08 找到 0 张图片:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":236,"aggregated":"从 https://www.msn.com/zh-cn/news/other/%E5%88%98%E4%BA%A6%E8%8F%B2%E4%BA%AE%E7%9B%B8%E5%B7%B4%E9%BB%8E%E6%97%B6%E8%A3%85%E5%91%A8%E9%80%A0%E5%9E%8B%E6%B5%AA%E6%BC%AB-%E4%B8%80%E4%B8%8B%E8%BD%A6%E4%BE%BF%E5%BC%95%E5%85%A8%E5%9C%BA%E6%AC%A2%E5%91%BC-%E5%85%A5%E5%9C%BA%E6%97%B6%E9%A3%9E%E5%90%BB%E8%BF%B7%E4%BA%BA/ar-AA1XWR08 找到 0 张图片:","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773235551365}}
{"type":"message","id":"de83f9d4","parentId":"120dc23d","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:26:09.529Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It found 0 images. Possibly the page uses JavaScript to load images, or the content is behind some script. Let's try another article. Or perhaps the og:image is in a meta tag with capital letters? Use case-insensitive? Also msn may have lazy loading with data-src. But our simple regex may have failed due to the HTML encoding.\n\nWe could fetch the page via curl and inspect manually. But maybe easier: use a Chinese image search engine like Sogou Images? But blocked.\n\nAlternatively, we could use a direct image search query for a known image host. Or we could search for recent Liu Yifei photos on March 10 by searching for the event: \"刘亦菲 巴黎时装周 3月10日\". There might be image results from Weibo or other sites.\n\nMaybe we can use the `oracle` skill to retrieve images? No.\n\nMaybe we can use `news` to get image URLs. But earlier we fetched news via DuckDuckGo; those articles may contain images but parsing HTML from remote is tricky.\n\nSimplify: Provide the user with links to the news articles that contain photos, so they can view them themselves. That's \"collecting\" photos in a sense. But they ask for \"最新照片\" (latest photos). They might expect actual image URLs. But maybe they just want to see the photos. I could also output the og:image from each article if available, because many articles have a featured image. Let's try to fetch the og:image for each URL we already have.\n\nWe have several URLs. I'll try them with a script that extracts og:image and some img tags. But it's more reliable to fetch the HTML and look for <meta property=\"og:image\">. Many news sites include that.\n\nLet's code a multi-URL fetcher that tries to get og:image. We'll also set a User-Agent header to be safe.\n\nBut if the pages are blocked by robots or require JS, we may get nothing.\n\nWe could also try to use a service like https://r.jina.ai/http://url to get simplified article content (Jina AI summarizer) but that's not an image source.\n\nAlternatively, we can search for \"刘亦菲 3月10日 图片\" on a site that returns static images like imgur or something? But not.\n\nMaybe we can use the Chinese microblogging site Weibo. Searching for her name with date might give images. But need to parse HTML.\n\nGiven the time, perhaps I should output the list of news articles (which include images) and note that the images can be viewed on those pages. That's acceptable: We've collected the latest photos indirectly.\n\nBut to better fulfill \"搜集照片\", I can try to extract image URLs from the HTML of each article using a more robust method: parse with a proper HTML parser like BeautifulSoup, but that might not be installed. However, we can use Python's html.parser from standard library? We can use `html.parser` module. Or we can use regex with more patterns.\n\nWe can also try to use the `requests` library? Not guaranteed. Use `urllib.request`.\n\nLet's try a different approach: Use the `news` API that might provide images. But we don't have that.\n\nMaybe we can use the `openclaw` tool `clawbot` for something? Not.\n\nGiven constraints, I'll attempt to parse the MSN article using a regex that matches og:image and maybe other tags with a case-insensitive approach. The earlier regex was case-sensitive? Actually property=\"og:image\" is exactly as typed; but some sites use \"og:image\" (lowercase). It's fine. But maybe the HTML is minified and the meta tag is different.\n\nLet's get a snippet of the fetched HTML if possible. I'll modify the script to store and print first 2000 characters for debugging. But easier: just output the og:image via grep. We can use curl and then grep -i. But the earlier fetch returned 0 images. Could be the page is compressed or encoded differently.\n\nI'll try to fetch using curl and see what we got. I'll capture the output.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d32d4349854f4d459afce9f0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -A \"Mozilla/5.0\" \"https://www.msn.com/zh-cn/news/other/%E5%88%98%E4%BA%A6%E8%8F%B2%E4%BA%AE%E7%9B%B8%E5%B7%B4%E9%BB%8E%E6%97%B6%E8%A3%85%E5%91%A8%E9%80%A0%E5%9E%8B%E6%B5%AA%E6%BC%AB-%E4%B8%80%E4%B8%8B%E8%BD%A6%E4%BE%BF%E5%BC%95%E5%85%A8%E5%9C%BA%E6%AC%A2%E5%91%BC-%E5%85%A5%E5%9C%BA%E6%97%B6%E9%A3%9E%E5%90%BB%E8%BF%B7%E4%BA%BA/ar-AA1XWR08\" -D - | head -n 20","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":32485,"output":2119,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34604,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235551369}}
