{"type":"message","id":"47625fac","parentId":"1098abb6","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:26:21.834Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Maybe the og:image is set via JavaScript. Let's try to find any <img> tags with src containing a jpg/png. But the page might be huge; we need to extract some image URLs.\n\nAlternatively, look for data-src or srcset.\n\nWe could use a different source: many Chinese news sites have images. Could try to fetch the NetEase article (163.com) which often includes images in the article body.\n\nLet's try the 163.com URL: https://www.163.com/dy/article/JGA8UD0Q05566SDO.html\n\nWe'll fetch it and search for image URLs. Typically, 163.com uses <img> tags with src.\n\nI'll script for multiple URLs.\n\nBut before diving deep, maybe the simplest: Provide a list of the article URLs that contain photos. The user asked \"搜集3月10日的刘亦菲最新照片\" – I can say: I've found several news articles from March 10 that include photos, here are the links. That's a kind of collection of photos (via links). That may suffice.\n\nIf they expect direct image URLs, I could attempt to extract them but risk failure.\n\nI'll check if the 163.com article actually includes photos by searching manually.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9b734438e37c4d769d55854a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -A \"Mozilla/5.0\" \"https://www.163.com/dy/article/JGA8UD0Q05566SDO.html\" | grep -Eo 'https?://[^\\s\"\\']+?\\.(jpg|jpeg|png|gif|webp)' | head -n 10","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":34668,"output":651,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35319,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235575658}}
