{"type":"message","id":"fb1fcd7b","parentId":"6f7789fb","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:26:30.631Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The syntax issue due to using single quotes inside the curl command with double quotes? Actually I'm using double quotes for the string, then single quotes inside. That should be okay. But the error says unexpected token '(' near line. Possibly the shell is interpreting parentheses? The pattern uses parentheses which need escaping in basic regex? In grep -E, parentheses are used for grouping. But the pattern is inside single quotes, so should be fine. However, the whole command is in double quotes within the exec? Actually, I'm passing a command string to exec; it will be run via bash -c. The quoting can be tricky. I need to ensure the command string is properly escaped. Since I'm in a Python heredoc? Actually I'm using exec with a command string. The string is passed directly to the shell. I need to escape the single quotes properly. Could also use double quotes inside with backslash.\n\nSimplify: Use Python to avoid shell quoting issues.\n\nLet's write a Python script that fetches a given URL and extracts image URLs (by regex). We'll test on the 163.com URL.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8195facd0e284fcf8e6d885a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nimport re, subprocess, urllib.parse, ssl, sys\nssl._create_default_https_context = ssl._create_unverified_context\n\nurl = \"https://www.163.com/dy/article/JGA8UD0Q05566SDO.html\"\n# fetch using curl? Use urllib directly for simplicity\ntry:\n    import urllib.request\n    req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0'})\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=15) as resp:\n        html = resp.read().decode('utf-8', errors='ignore')\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Fetch error: {e}\")\n    sys.exit(1)\n\n# regex for image URLs: src=\"http...jpg/png...\"\nimgs = re.findall(r'https?://[^\\s\"\\'>]+?\\.(?:jpg|jpeg|png|gif|webp)', html, re.I)\n# deduplicate\nseen = set()\nunique = []\nfor i in imgs:\n    if i not in seen:\n        seen.add(i)\n        unique.append(i)\nprint(f\"Found {len(unique)} image URLs from {url}\")\nfor u in unique[:15]:\n    print(u)\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":35168,"output":795,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35963,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235581863}}
