{"type":"message","id":"fe5376fa","parentId":"b1a0b888","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:26:52.200Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Great! We found many image URLs from the 163.com article. The URLs include nimg.ws.126.net with encoded actual URLs. We need to resolve these to actual image URLs because many are wrapped. For example:\n\n`https://nimg.ws.126.net/?url=http://cms-bucket.ws.126.net/2026/0310/7a243248j00tbookw004cc000u000mic.jpg`\n\nWe need to extract the `url` parameter and then use that as the actual image URL. Or we can directly use that URL but it may redirect. The `nimg.ws.126.net` is an image proxy that serves the image from the original location; we can likely use it directly. But it's better to get the original URL for persistence.\n\nWe can parse the query parameter `url` which is base64? Actually it's plain URL-encoded. So we need to decode. Let's extract the `url` parameter and then use that. Some are direct jpg/png from cms-bucket.ws.126.net.\n\nBut the ask: collect photos. We can provide the direct image links (the ones that are actual images). The nimg.ws.126.net URLs are likely direct image links after following redirect, but they contain the encoded original. We could provide the original URL by extracting the `url` param and then unquoting. However, we could also just provide the nimg URLs; they should show the image when accessed. That might be enough.\n\nWe also have other article URLs. We can extract images from the other articles: the Tencent news article, the Sina article, the The Paper article, etc. Let's gather from a few to provide a variety.\n\nBetter: iterate over each article URL from our list, extract image URLs, and then deduplicate across all.\n\nBut note: we must only include photos from March 10. The article dates: we know some articles mention March 10. Our news list includes several with March 10 dates. Let's identify which URLs are from March 10 based on the snippets:\n\n- MSN article: \"3月10日，巴黎时装周...\" -> that's March 10.\n- NetEase: It mentions \"11月5日\" (November) but also mentions \"出道22年\" - not necessarily March 10. Actually snippet says \"就在11月5日这天，37岁的刘亦菲突然在深夜高调宣布喜讯。\" That's November, not March. The article date likely is more recent but the content is about past event. The article may be published on a recent date (maybe March). Hard to tell. The snippet doesn't show date. But the URL doesn't contain date. We need to check the publish date; not critical maybe, but we want March 10 photos.\n\n- Tencent article: \"2年未拍戏却不急，刘亦菲还在等好剧本\" – no explicit date. Possibly March? We'll assume it's recent.\n\n- Sina article about LV show mentions March 10? Possibly. The snippet: \"#刘亦菲花瓣裙气场全开#\" likely from March 10.\n\n- Another Sina article about LV: \"路易威登2026秋冬女装大秀前夕，品牌全球代言人刘亦菲第八次启程巴黎\" likely dated around March 10.\n\n- The Paper: \"37岁刘亦菲最新状态冲上热搜，皮肤引热议，本人回应\" – the snippet says \"活动上，刘亦菲穿一身白裙...\" might be from March 10.\n\n- Sohu: \"和宋承宪分开7年后，37岁刘亦菲深夜高调宣布喜讯\" – that refers to November, not March.\n\n- Sina again: \"刘亦菲巴黎看秀造型曝光，居家短裙装引回忆\" explicitly shows date: \"2026年03月10日 10:15\".\n\nSo we have at least three articles explicitly referencing March 10: MSN, Sina (the one with date 2026年03月10日), and possibly the other Sina (the one about LV show). Also The Paper might be on that date.\n\nThus we can extract images from those.\n\nBut extraction from each might be done similarly. Let's target the three URLs with clear March 10 relevance:\n\n- MSN: https://www.msn.com/.../ar-AA1XWR08\n- Sina: https://k.sina.com.cn/article_1283367840_m4c7ea3a003301lkce.html (the one with date)\n- Another Sina: https://k.sina.com.cn/article_1496814565_m593793e503301yno8.html (maybe about LV)\n- The Paper: https://m.thepaper.cn/newsdetail_forward_30726868\n\nWe can also include Tencent and 163 if they have March 10 images. But to be safe, we can just extract from those that are March 10.\n\nLet's write a Python script to fetch a list of URLs and extract image URLs using regex pattern, then clean them.\n\nBut we also need to handle the fact that some sites may block non-browser requests or require TLS handshake. We'll use urllib with proper headers.\n\nLet's code in a single script.\n\nBut also, we need to present the result to the user in Chinese. So we can output a list of images with titles (maybe use alt text? That would be nicer). We can also attempt to extract the alt attribute for context.\n\nSimplify: For each article, provide a heading with source and date, then list image URLs.\n\nLet's try to fetch the Sina article with date.\n\nBut first, note that the environment may have restrictions on SNI? It seems fine as we've fetched.\n\nProceed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_620f8a6e42a74f9c8eae3026","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nimport re, urllib.request, ssl, sys\nssl._create_default_https_context = ssl._create_unverified_context\n\n# List of article URLs that likely contain March 10 photos\nurls = [\n    (\"MSN\", \"https://www.msn.com/zh-cn/news/other/%E5%88%98%E4%BA%A6%E8%8F%B2%E4%BA%AE%E7%9B%B8%E5%B7%B4%E9%BB%8E%E6%97%B6%E8%A3%85%E5%91%A8%E9%80%A0%E5%9E%8B%E6%B5%AA%E6%BC%AB-%E4%B8%80%E4%B8%8B%E8%BD%A6%E4%BE%BF%E5%BC%95%E5%85%A8%E5%9C%BA%E6%AC%A2%E5%91%BC-%E5%85%A5%E5%9C%BA%E6%97%B6%E9%A3%9E%E5%90%BB%E8%BF%B7%E4%BA%BA/ar-AA1XWR08\"),\n    (\"Sina\", \"https://k.sina.com.cn/article_1283367840_m4c7ea3a003301lkce.html\"),\n    (\"Sina2\", \"https://k.sina.com.cn/article_1496814565_m593793e503301yno8.html\"),\n    (\"The Paper\", \"https://m.thepaper.cn/newsdetail_forward_30726868\")\n]\n\nheaders = {'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/120.0 Safari/537.36'}\n\nall_imgs = set()\nfor name, url in urls:\n    try:\n        req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers=headers)\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=20) as resp:\n            html = resp.read().decode('utf-8', errors='ignore')\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error fetching {name}: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        continue\n\n    # Extract img src\n    imgs = re.findall(r'https?://[^\\s\"\\'<>]+?\\.(?:jpg|jpeg|png|gif|webp)', html, re.I)\n    # also maybe data-src?\n    imgs += re.findall(r'data-src=[\"\\']([^\"\\']+\\.(?:jpg|jpeg|png|gif|webp))[\"\\']', html, re.I)\n    # Clean: remove tracking params? Keep as is.\n    filtered = []\n    for i in imgs:\n        # decode HTML entities\n        i = urllib.parse.unquote(i)\n        # sometimes there is &amp; etc\n        i = i.replace('&amp;', '&')\n        if i and not i.startswith('data:'):\n            all_imgs.add(i)\n    print(f\"{name}: found {len(imgs)} raw, total unique so far: {len(all_imgs)}\")\n\nprint(f\"\\nTotal unique image URLs: {len(all_imgs)}\\n\")\nfor img in sorted(all_imgs)[:20]:\n    print(img)\nPYEOF","timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":36382,"output":3271,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39653,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773235591722}}
