{"type":"message","id":"66f6b355","parentId":"b33fa7f7","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:51:06.794Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config set command fails because \"tavily-search\" is not recognized as a top-level skill config key. Need to see what the correct path is. Possibly the skill name is different or the config uses a different structure. Let's check the installed skill's location and its SKILL.md to understand the proper config path.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"The key path might be different. Let's check the skill's structure:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3c99ffe0b8784e30a8c56543","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-tavily-search/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":41849,"output":208,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42057,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773237063212}}
{"type":"message","id":"2a4d7207","parentId":"66f6b355","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:51:06.808Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3c99ffe0b8784e30a8c56543","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: tavily-search\ndescription: \"Web search via Tavily API (alternative to Brave). Use when the user asks to search the web / look up sources / find links and Brave web_search is unavailable or undesired. Returns a small set of relevant results (title, url, snippet) and can optionally include short answer summaries.\"\n---\n\n# Tavily Search\n\nUse the bundled script to search the web with Tavily.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Provide API key via either:\n  - environment variable: `TAVILY_API_KEY`, or\n  - `~/.openclaw/.env` line: `TAVILY_API_KEY=...`\n\n## Commands\n\nRun from the OpenClaw workspace:\n\n```bash\n# raw JSON (default)\npython3 {baseDir}/scripts/tavily_search.py --query \"...\" --max-results 5\n\n# include short answer (if available)\npython3 {baseDir}/scripts/tavily_search.py --query \"...\" --max-results 5 --include-answer\n\n# stable schema (closer to web_search): {query, results:[{title,url,snippet}], answer?}\npython3 {baseDir}/scripts/tavily_search.py --query \"...\" --max-results 5 --format brave\n\n# human-readable Markdown list\npython3 {baseDir}/scripts/tavily_search.py --query \"...\" --max-results 5 --format md\n```\n\n## Output\n\n### raw (default)\n- JSON: `query`, optional `answer`, `results: [{title,url,content}]`\n\n### brave\n- JSON: `query`, optional `answer`, `results: [{title,url,snippet}]`\n\n### md\n- A compact Markdown list with title/url/snippet.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Keep `max-results` small by default (3–5) to reduce token/reading load.\n- Prefer returning URLs + snippets; fetch full pages only when needed.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773237066802}}
{"type":"message","id":"cfe86b23","parentId":"2a4d7207","timestamp":"2026-03-11T13:51:11.468Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The skill reads API key from environment variable `TAVILY_API_KEY` or from `~/.openclaw/.env`. So we don't need to set it in openclaw.json. Instead, set it in the environment file or export it.\n\nLet's set it in the .env file. We need to check if the .env exists and then add the line or update it. The path is `~/.openclaw/.env`. Since this is a sensitive key, we should handle it carefully.\n\nWe could:\n- append to ~/.openclaw/.env if it exists, or create it\n- ensure no duplicates\n\nLet's check if .env exists and then add.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"The skill gets its API key from the environment variable `TAVILY_API_KEY` or from `~/.openclaw/.env`. Let's set it properly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dc0d285cb31e438b8998915f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p ~/.openclaw && echo 'TAVILY_API_KEY=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' >> ~/.openclaw/.env"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":42399,"output":398,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42797,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773237066806}}
