{"type":"message","id":"3aeba7a0","parentId":"61374a5e","timestamp":"2026-03-11T14:04:21.289Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Installed successfully. Now I need to create an OpenClaw skill wrapper for agent-browser. The skill should define commands that call the agent-browser CLI. Let's create a minimal skill:\n\nSkill directory: `/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-browser`\n- SKILL.md: description\n- scripts/agent_browser.py (or .js) that calls the agent-browser binary\n\nBut the skill system expects a certain structure. Let's look at another skill example. Maybe the `clawhub install` would have created that structure. We can mimic that.\n\nSince we can't get the exact skill from ClawHub due to rate limits, we can manually create a simple skill that runs `agent-browser` with appropriate arguments.\n\nAlternatively, maybe we can directly use the `agent-browser` CLI from OpenClaw via exec calls without needing a skill? The user might want to use it as a skill for automation.\n\nGiven constraints, I'll create a simple skill:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"现在手动创建 `agent-browser` 技能包装："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0b4e379b7e514e70bfd49d01","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-browser/SKILL.md","content":"---\nname: agent-browser\ndescription: \"Headless browser automation for AI agents. Control a headless browser via CLI (based on Playwright/WebDriver). Use when you need to: navigate to a URL, take a screenshot, extract text, click elements, or run scripts in a browser context.\"\n---\n\n# Agent Browser\n\nUse the `agent-browser` CLI to automate browser tasks.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- The `agent-browser` binary must be installed (globally or in PATH). Install with:\n  ```bash\n  npm install -g agent-browser\n  ```\n\n## Commands\n\nRun from the OpenClaw workspace:\n\n```bash\n# Navigate to a URL (and wait for load)\nagent-browser open https://example.com\n\n# Take a screenshot\nagent-browser screenshot --output /tmp/screenshot.png\n\n# Extract page text\nagent-browser text\n\n# Click a CSS selector\nagent-browser click \"button.submit\"\n\n# Evaluate JavaScript and return result\nagent-browser eval \"document.title\"\n\n# Run a custom script file\nagent-browser run script.js\n```\n\nNotes:\n- The tool manages a headless Chromium instance via Playwright.\n- It supports multiple sessions (contexts). Use `--context` to separate.\n- For long-running agents, consider starting a persistent session: `agent-browser start` then reuse with `agent-browser connect`.\n\nSee `agent-browser --help` for full options."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":66426,"output":806,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67232,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773237853733}}
