{"type":"message","id":"e886cb39","parentId":"31056798","timestamp":"2026-03-12T03:07:55.654Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API returns 404 - Not Found. Could be because the repository is brand new and Pages needs to be enabled. Let me try a different approach: create a `docs` folder or use `gh` command to set the Pages branch.\n\nAlternatively, use GitHub's web interface manually. But as an assistant, I can use the `gh api` correctly - maybe I need to use the correct endpoint.\n\nActually, the correct endpoint is:\nPUT /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pages\nwith body: {\"source\":{\"branch\":\"main\",\"path\":\"/\"}}\n\nBut maybe it's not available for this user/plan? Or maybe we need to use a different method. Let me check if Pages is already enabled.\n\nI can also do:\ngh api -X GET repos/simplewei/maplestory-2d/pages\n\nIf it returns \"null\" or not found, we need to create it.\n\nLet me try the GET first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6452daf4e60041d98902818f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh api -X GET repos/simplewei/maplestory-2d/pages 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":92859,"output":453,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93312,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773284870899}}
