{"type":"message","id":"e1f9f869","parentId":"071495d5","timestamp":"2026-03-12T03:08:01.886Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Pages API returns 404, which suggests the Pages site hasn't been created yet. I might need to use an authenticated token with proper scope. My token has many scopes including admin:repo_hook, but maybe it needs `repo` scope (which it has) and `public_repo`? I have all those.\n\nAlternatively, maybe the repository needs to be completely set up first; sometimes it takes a few seconds. Let me try verifying the repository is visible first, then try to enable Pages via a simpler method: using the `gh` command that does this automatically? Actually `gh` has a `repo create` but not `pages enable`.\n\nAnother way: create a `docs` folder and set branch to `gh-pages`. I'll create a `docs` folder with the same index.html and set the branch to `gh-pages`. Let's do that manually:\n\n1. Create a `docs` folder in the repo\n2. Copy files there\n3. Commit and push to `gh-pages` branch\n4. Or configure Pages to serve from `main` branch `/` - but API 404 maybe because the app doesn't have the feature? Possibly because it's an organization or plan restriction? Hmm.\n\nMaybe I can just create a `gh-pages` branch; GitHub Pages will auto-deploy from it.\n\nLet me try that: create a gh-pages branch with the game files.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"我们采用经典方案：推送代码到 `gh-pages` 分支，GitHub Pages 会自动部署。\n\n步骤：复制 `main` 分支内容到 `gh-pages` 分支并推送："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dd1b0269b79d4c92b0b7ca09","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/maplestory-game && git checkout -b gh-pages && git push origin gh-pages && git checkout main","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":93176,"output":709,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93885,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReaso